Small shop:

An enterprising Bulgarian opens neighborhood shops in several cities and sells at different prices:



city / product     coffee water beer sweets peanuts

Sofia              0.50   0.80  1.20  1.45  1.60

Plovdiv            0.40   0.70  1.15  1.30  1.50

Varna              0.45   0.70  1.10  1.35  1.55



Write a program that reads product (string), city (string) and quantity (decimal number) entered by the user and calculates and prints how much the corresponding quantity of the selected product costs in the specified city.